..............}}}{, Deceased}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084\sa0\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~}}}{NOTICE OF OPENING}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084\sa0\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~}}}{ADMINISTRATION OF}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084\sa0\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~}}}{ESTATE, OF APPOINTMENT OF}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084\sa0\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~}}}{ADMINISTRATOR, AND}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084\sa0\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~}}}{NOTICE TO CREDITOR}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084\sa0\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{To the Department of Health and Human Services Who May Be Interested in the Estate of }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{....................}}}{, Deceased, who died on or about }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{........................}}}{ (date):}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084\sa0\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{You are hereby notified that on the }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{........}}}{ day of }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{............}}}{ (month), }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{............}}}{ (year), an intestate estate was opened in the above-named court and that }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{....................}}}{ was appointed administrator of the estate.}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084\sa0\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{You are further notified that the birthdate of the deceased is }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{............}}}{ and the deceased\u8217\'3fs social security number is...-...-.... The name of the spouse is }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{................................}}}{. The birthdate of the spouse is }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{............}}}{ and the spouse\u8217\'3fs social security number is...-...-...., and that the spouse of the deceased is alive as of the date of this notice, or deceased as of }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{........................}}}{ (date).}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084\sa0\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{You are further notified that the deceased was/was not a disabled or a blind child of the medical assistance recipient by the name of }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{....................}}}{, who had a birthdate of }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{............}}}{ and a social security number of...-...-...., and the medical assistance debt of that medical assistance recipient was waived pursuant to }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 249A.53, subsection 2}}}{, paragraph }{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fa\u8221\'3f}}}{, subparagraph (1), and is now collectible from this estate pursuant to }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 249A.53, subsection 2}}}{, paragraph }{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fb\u8221\'3f}}}{.}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084\sa0\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{Notice is hereby given that if the department of health and human services has a claim against the estate for the deceased person or persons named in this notice, the claim shall be filed with the clerk of the above-named district court, as provided by law, duly authenticated, for allowance, within six months from the date of sending this notice and, unless otherwise allowed or paid, the claim is thereafter forever barred. If the department does not have a claim, the department shall return the notice to the administrator with notification stating the department does not have a claim within six months from the date of sending this notice.}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084\sa0\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{Dated this }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{........}}}{ day of }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{............}}}{ (month), }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{............}}}{ (year)}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084\sa0\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~}}}{....................}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084\sa0\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~}}}{Administrator of the estate}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084\sa0\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~}}}{....................}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084\sa0\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~}}}{Address}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084\sa0\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084{....................}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084\sa0\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084{Attorney for the administrator}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084\sa0\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084{....................}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084\sa0\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084{Address}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084\sa0\par}{\pard\plain\f5\fs8\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084\par}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{2001 Acts, ch 109, \'a71}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2002 Acts, ch 1119, \'a797}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2007 Acts, ch 134, \'a711}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2010 Acts, ch 1137, \'a74}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2011 Acts, ch 34, \'a7139}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2016 Acts, ch 1073, \'a7171}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2023 Acts, ch 19, \'a71275}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\keep\keepn\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0\cbpat2{Referred to in }{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{\'a7633.410}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 635.13}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\keep\f5\fs18\qj\fi0\sb260\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\qj{633.232 through 633.235}}}{Reserved.}{\f5\fs18\qj\chcbpat2}{\f5\fs18\qj}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\fi0\ri0\li0{\f5\fs18\chcbpat2}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\qc\fi0\sb360\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\qc{SUBCHAPTER V}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keep\keepn\f5\fs18\qc\fi0\sb120\ri0\li0{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E1_30_2E2_2E2}{RIGHTS OF SURVIVING SPOUSE}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E1_30_2E2_2E2}\par}{}{\pard\plain\keep\keepn\f5\fs12\qc\fi0\sb140\ri0\li0\cbpat2{Referred to in }{{\f5\fs12\qc{\'a7249A.3}}}\par}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\qc\fi0\sb360\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\qc{PART 1}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keep\keepn\f5\fs18\qc\fi0\sb120\ri0\li0{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E1_30_2E4_2E1_2E2}{RIGHT TO TAKE AGAINST THE WILL}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E1_30_2E4_2E1_2E2}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb360\ri0\li0}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0\cbpat2\par}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0\cbpat2\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{633.236}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E1_30_2E4_2E2_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E1_30_2E4_2E2_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Right of elective share of surviving spouse.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{When a married person domiciled in Iowa at the time of death dies, the surviving spouse shall have the right to take an elective share under the provisions of }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{sections 633.237 through 633.246}}}{. If the surviving spouse has a conservator, the court may authorize or direct the conservator to elect the share as the court deems appropriate under the circumstances.}\par}{}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{[C51, \'a71407; R60, \'a72435; C73, \'a72452; C97, \'a73376; S13, \'a73376; C24, 27, 31, 35, 39, \'a7}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{12006, 12010;}}}{ C46, 50, 54, 58, 62, \'a7636.21, 636.25; C66, 71, 73, 75, 77, 79, }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{81, \'a7633.236}}}{]}\par}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{88 Acts, ch 1064, \'a71}}}{; }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{2005 Acts, ch 38, \'a712}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\keep\keepn\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0\cbpat2{Referred to in }{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{\'a7633.237}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 633.245}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 633.246}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 633.247}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 633.264}}}\par}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj}{Effect on medical assistance eligibility, see }{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{\'a7249A.3(11)}}}{ and }{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{633.246A}}}{ }\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb219\ri0\li0}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0\cbpat2\par}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0\cbpat2\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{633.237}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E1_30_2E4_2E3_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E1_30_2E4_2E3_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Presumption against filing elective share.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{1.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Following the appointment of a personal representative of the estate of the decedent, the personal representative shall cause to be served a written notice upon the surviving spouse pursuant to }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 633.40, subsection 5}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, notifying the surviving spouse that unless, within four months after service of the notice, the spouse files an election in writing with the clerk of court electing the share as set forth in }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 633.236}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ and }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{sections 633.238 through 633.246}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, the spouse shall be deemed to take under the will or to receive the intestate share. If, within the four-month period following service of the notice, an affidavit is filed setting forth that the surviving spouse is incapable of making the election and does not have a conservator, the personal representative shall make application to the court for an order pursuant to }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 633.244}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{2.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Following the death of a settlor of a revocable trust, the trustee of such revocable trust shall cause to be served a written notice upon the surviving spouse pursuant to }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 633.40, subsection 5}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, notifying the surviving spouse that unless, within four months after service of the notice, the spouse files an election with the trustee electing the share as set forth in }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 633.236}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ and }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{sections 633.238 through 633.246}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, the spouse shall be deemed to take under the terms of the revocable trust. If, within the four-month period following service of the notice, an affidavit is filed setting forth that the surviving spouse is incapable of making the election and does not have a conservator, the trustee shall make application to the court for an order pursuant to }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 633.244}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{3.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{If the surviving spouse has a conservator, notice shall be given to the conservator and the spouse pursuant to }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{subsections 1 and 2}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{4.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{The notice provisions under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{subsections 1 and 2}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ are not applicable if the surviving spouse or the spouse\u8217\'3fs conservator files, at any time, an election to take under the will, receive the intestate share, or take under the revocable trust. If the surviving spouse fails to file an election under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{this section}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ within four months of the date notice is served, it shall be conclusively presumed that the surviving spouse elects to take under the will, receive the intestate share, or take under the revocable trust.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{5.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Upon application of the surviving spouse or the spouse\u8217\'3fs conservator filed before the time for making the election expires, the court may extend the period in which the surviving spouse may make the election.}}}\par}{}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{[C73, \'a72452; C97, \'a73376; S13, \'a73376; C24, 27, 31, 35, 39, \'a7}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{12007, 12010;}}}{ C46, 50, 54, 58, 62, \'a7636.22, 636.25; C66, 71, 73, 75, 77, 79, }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{81, \'a7633.237}}}{]}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{84 Acts, ch 1080, \'a73}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 88 Acts, ch 1064, \'a72}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2005 Acts, ch 38, \'a713}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2009 Acts, ch 52, \'a73, 14}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2012 Acts, ch 1123, \'a73, 32}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\keep\keepn\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0\cbpat2{Referred to in }{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{\'a7633.236}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 633.241}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 633.246}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 633A.3110}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 635.13}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb219\ri0\li0}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0\cbpat2\par}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0\cbpat2\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{633.238}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E1_30_2E4_2E4_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E1_30_2E4_2E4_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Elective share of surviving spouse.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{1.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{The elective share of the surviving spouse shall be limited to all of the following:}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{a.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{One-third in value of all the legal or equitable estates in real property possessed by the decedent at any time during the marriage which have not been sold on execution or other judicial sale, and to which the surviving spouse has made no express written relinquishment of right, including but not limited to any relinquishments of rights described in paragraph }}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fd\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{b.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{All personal property that, at the time of death, was in the hands of the decedent as the head of a family, exempt from execution.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{c.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{One-third of all personal property of the decedent that is not necessary for the payment of debts and charges.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{d.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{(1)}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{One-third in value of the property held in trust not necessary for the payment of debts and charges over which the decedent was a settlor and retained at the time of death the power to alter, amend, or revoke the trust, or over which the decedent waived or rescinded any such power within one year of the date of death, and to which the surviving spouse has not made any express written relinquishment in compliance with subparagraph (2).}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{(2)}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{The elective share of the surviving spouse shall not include the value of the property held in a trust described in subparagraph (1), if both of the following are true:}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{(a)}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{The decedent created the trust after the date of decedent\u8217\'3fs marriage to the surviving spouse.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{(b)}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Every transfer of property into the trust, except for tangible personal property, included a written statement which complied with this subparagraph division. The written statement shall be in boldface type of a minimum size of ten points, signed and dated by the surviving spouse with a valid notarial acknowledgment, and in substantially the following form:}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084{{\f5\b0\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\ul0\strike0{\~\~\~}}}{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj}{By signing below, I acknowledge that I am giving up all rights to enjoyment of the property described above, regardless of whether or not I survive my spouse and regardless of any rights Iowa law otherwise gives to me with respect to such property. I am specifically waiving my elective share in the property described in this waiver.}{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj}\par}{}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084{{\f5\b0\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\ul0\strike0{\~\~\~}}}{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj}{This waiver shall apply regardless of any changes made to the trust in the future, including any change to the beneficiaries of the trust.}{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\fs8\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{2.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{When a settlor of a revocable trust transfers real property to the trustee of the revocable trust and the settlor\u8217\'3fs spouse signs a conveyance of the real property to such trustee which includes a general waiver of rights of dower, homestead, and distributive share, the spouse is only relinquishing the right to that real property and its value under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{subsection 1}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, paragraph }}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fa\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, for the purpose of conveying marketable title to a subsequent purchaser from the trustee and is not relinquishing the right to the value of the real estate under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{subsection 1}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, paragraph }}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fd\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, unless the spouse specifically states in writing an intent to relinquish the right to the value of the real estate under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{subsection 1}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, paragraph }}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fd\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{. The relinquishment of right under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{subsection 1}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, paragraph }}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fa\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ shall not prevent the surviving spouse from electing one-third in value of such real property under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{subsection 1}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, paragraph }}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fd\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{3.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{The elective share described in }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{this section}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ shall be in lieu of any property the spouse would otherwise receive under the last will and testament of the decedent, through intestacy, or under the terms of a revocable trust.}}}\par}{}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{[C51, \'a71329, 1390, 1394, 1421; R60, \'a72361, 2422, 2477, 2479; C73, \'a72371, 2436, 2440; C97, \'a73312, 3362, 3366; C24, 27, 31, 35, 39, \'a7}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{11918, 11986, 11990, 11991;}}}{ C46, 50, 54, 58, 62, \'a7635.7, 636.1, 636.5, 636.6; C66, 71, 73, 75, 77, 79, }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{81, \'a7633.238}}}{]}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{2005 Acts, ch 38, \'a714}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2009 Acts, ch 52, \'a74, 14}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2015 Acts, ch 125, \'a74, 7}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\keep\keepn\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0\cbpat2{Referred to in }{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{\'a7614.14}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 633.236}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 633.237}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 633.239}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 633.240}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 633.246}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb219\ri0\li0{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\chcbpat2}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{633.239}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E1_30_2E4_2E5_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E1_30_2E4_2E5_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Share to embrace homestead.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{The share of the surviving spouse in such real estate shall be set off in such manner as to include the homestead, or so much thereof as will be equal to the share allotted to the spouse pursuant to }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 633.238}}}{ unless the spouse prefers a different arrangement, but no such different arrangement shall be allowed unless there is sufficient property remaining to pay the claims and charges against the decedent\u8217\'3fs estate.}\par}{}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{[C51, \'a71395; R60, \'a72426; C73, \'a72441; C97, \'a73367; C24, 27, 31, 35, 39, \'a7}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{11992;}}}{ C46, 50, 54, 58, 62, \'a7636.7; C66, 71, 73, 75, 77, 79, }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{81, \'a7633.239}}}{]}\par}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{2005 Acts, ch 38, \'a715}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\keep\keepn\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0\cbpat2{Referred to in }{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{\'a7633.236}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 633.237}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb219\ri0\li0{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\chcbpat2}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{633.240}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E1_30_2E4_2E6_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E1_30_2E4_2E6_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Election to receive homestead.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{In estates in which the surviving spouse has filed an election and in all intestate estates, whether an election is filed or not, the surviving spouse or the spouse\u8217\'3fs conservator, if applicable, may, in lieu of the spouse\u8217\'3fs share in the real property possessed by the decedent at any time during the marriage, which has not been sold on execution or other judicial sale, and to which the surviving spouse has made no express written relinquishment of right, elect to receive a life estate in the homestead. Such election shall be made and entered of record as provided in }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 633.245}}}{. In making such election, the surviving spouse shall have all the rights as to the personal property provided in }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 633.238, subsection 1}}}{, paragraphs }{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fb\u8221\'3f}}}{, }{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fc\u8221\'3f}}}{, and }{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fd\u8221\'3f}}}{. In case of failure to make such election, the right to receive the life estate in the homestead shall be waived.}\par}{}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{[C97, \'a73377; S13, \'a73377; C24, 27, 31, 35, 39, \'a7}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{12012;}}}{ C46, 50, 54, 58, 62, \'a7636.27; C66, 71, 73, 75, 77, 79, }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{81, \'a7633.240}}}{]}\par}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{88 Acts, ch 1064, \'a73}}}{; }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{2005 Acts, ch 38, \'a716}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\keep\keepn\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0\cbpat2{Referred to in }{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{\'a7633.236}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 633.237}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 633.245}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 633.246}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb219\ri0\li0}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0\cbpat2\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{633.241}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E1_30_2E4_2E7_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E1_30_2E4_2E7_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Time for election to receive life estate in homestead.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{If the surviving spouse does not make an election to receive the life estate in the homestead and file it with the clerk within four months from the date of service of notice under }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 633.237}}}{, it shall be conclusively presumed that the surviving spouse waives the right to make the election. The court on application may, prior to the expiration of the period of four months, for cause shown, enter an order extending the time for making the election.}\par}{}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{[C97, \'a73377; S13, \'a73377; C24, 27, 31, 35, 39, \'a7}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{12013;}}}{ C46, 50, 54, 58, 62, \'a7636.28; C66, 71, 73, 75, 77, 79, }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{81, \'a7633.241}}}{]}\par}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{84 Acts, ch 1080, \'a74}}}{; }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{2005 Acts, ch 38, \'a717}}}{; }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{2008 Acts, ch 1119, \'a716, 39}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\keep\keepn\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0\cbpat2{Referred to in }{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{\'a7633.236}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 633.237}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb219\ri0\li0{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\chcbpat2}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{633.242}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E1_30_2E4_2E8_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E1_30_2E4_2E8_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Rights of election personal to surviving spouse.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{The right of the surviving spouse to take an elective share, and the right of the surviving spouse to receive a life estate in the homestead, are personal. They are not transferable and cannot be exercised for the spouse subsequent to the spouse\u8217\'3fs death. If the surviving spouse dies prior to filing an election, it shall be conclusively presumed that the surviving spouse does not take such elective share.}\par}{}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{[C66, 71, 73, 75, 77, 79, }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{81, \'a7633.242}}}{]}\par}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{2005 Acts, ch 38, \'a718}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\keep\keepn\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0\cbpat2{Referred to in }{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{\'a7633.236}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 633.237}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb219\ri0\li0{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\chcbpat2}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{633.243}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E1_30_2E4_2E9_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E1_30_2E4_2E9_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Filing elections.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{The filing of the elective share and the election to receive a life estate in the homestead shall be filed in the office of the clerk in which the decedent\u8217\'3fs estate is being administered and served on the trustee of the revocable trust. The court where the election is filed shall have exclusive jurisdiction over all matters regarding elections under }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{this chapter}}}{.}\par}{}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{[C24, 27, 31, 35, 39, \'a7}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{12010;}}}{ C46, 50, 54, 58, 62, \'a7636.25; C66, 71, 73, 75, 77, 79, }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{81, \'a7633.243}}}{]}\par}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{2005 Acts, ch 38, \'a719}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\keep\keepn\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0\cbpat2{Referred to in }{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{\'a7633.236}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 633.237}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb219\ri0\li0{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\chcbpat2}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{633.244}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E1_30_2E4_2E1_30_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E1_30_2E4_2E1_30_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Incompetent spouse \u8212\'3f election by court.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{In case an affidavit is filed that the surviving spouse is incapable of determining whether to take the elective share, or to elect to receive a life estate in the homestead, and does not have a conservator, the court shall fix a time and place of hearing on the matter and cause a notice thereof to be served upon the surviving spouse in such manner and for such time as the court may direct. At the hearing, a guardian ad litem shall be appointed to represent the spouse and the court shall enter such orders as it deems appropriate under the circumstances. The guardian ad litem shall be a practicing attorney.}\par}{}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{[S13, \'a73376, 3377; C24, 27, 31, 35, 39, \'a7}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{12011, 12014;}}}{ C46, 50, 54, 58, 62, \'a7636.26, 636.29; C66, 71, 73, 75, 77, 79, }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{81, \'a7633.244}}}{]}\par}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{88 Acts, ch 1064, \'a74}}}{; }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{90 Acts, ch 1271, \'a71513}}}{; }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{2005 Acts, ch 38, \'a720}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\keep\keepn\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0\cbpat2{Referred to in }{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{\'a7229.27}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 633.236}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 633.237}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 633.245}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 633.246}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb219\ri0\li0{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\chcbpat2}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{633.245}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E1_30_2E4_2E11_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E1_30_2E4_2E11_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Record of election.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{The elections of the surviving spouse under }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 633.236}}}{, }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{633.240}}}{, or }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{633.244}}}{ shall be entered on the proper records of the court.}\par}{}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{[C73, \'a72452; C97, \'a73376; S13, \'a73376; C24, 27, 31, 35, 39, \'a7}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{12008;}}}{ C46, 50, 54, 58, 62, \'a7636.23; C66, 71, 73, 75, 77, 79, }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{81, \'a7633.245}}}{]}\par}{}{\pard\plain\keep\keepn\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0\cbpat2{Referred to in }{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{\'a7633.236}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 633.237}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 633.240}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb219\ri0\li0}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0\cbpat2\par}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0\cbpat2\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{633.246}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E1_30_2E4_2E12_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E1_30_2E4_2E12_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Election not subject to change.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{1.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{An election by or on behalf of a surviving spouse to take the share provided in }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 633.211}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{633.212}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{633.236}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{633.238}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{633.240}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, or }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{633.244}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ shall be binding and shall not be subject to change except for such causes as would justify an equitable decree for the rescission of a deed.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{2.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{An affirmative election to take under the will, receive the intestate share, or take under the revocable trust shall be irrevocable when filed as provided in }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 633.237}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{.}}}\par}{}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{[C66, 71, 73, 75, 77, 79, }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{81, \'a7633.246}}}{]}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{2009 Acts, ch 52, \'a75, 14}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2012 Acts, ch 1123, \'a74, 32}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\keep\keepn\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0\cbpat2{Referred to in }{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{\'a7633.236}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 633.237}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb219\ri0\li0}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0\cbpat2\par}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0\cbpat2\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{633.246A}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E1_30_2E4_2E13_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E1_30_2E4_2E13_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Medical assistance eligibility.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{Unless precluded from doing so under the terms of a premarital agreement, the failure of a surviving spouse to make an election under }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{this subchapter}}}{ constitutes a transfer of assets for the purpose of determining eligibility for medical assistance pursuant to }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{chapter 249A}}}{ to the extent that the value received by making the election would have exceeded the value of property received absent the election.}\par}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{2000 Acts, ch 1060, \'a77}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2005 Acts, ch 38, \'a721}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2006 Acts, ch 1104, \'a72}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2018 Acts, ch 1041, \'a7127}}}\par}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\qc\fi0\sb360\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\qc{PART 2}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keep\keepn\f5\fs18\qc\fi0\sb120\ri0\li0{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E1_30_2E5_2E1_2E2}{PROCEDURE FOR SETTING OFF}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E1_30_2E5_2E1_2E2}\par}{\pard\plain\keep\keepn\f5\fs18\qc\fi0\ri0\li0\sa0\par}{\pard\plain\keep\keepn\f5\fs18\qc\fi0\ri0\li0{ELECTIVE SHARE}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb360\ri0\li0{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\chcbpat2}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{633.247}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E1_30_2E5_2E2_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E1_30_2E5_2E2_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Setting off elective share of surviving spouse.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{The share of the surviving spouse under }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 633.236}}}{ may be set off by the mutual consent of all parties in interest, or by referees appointed by the court. An application to have the share set off by referees shall be made by an interested party in writing by filing with the clerk of court. A copy of such application shall be sent to all interested parties.}\par}{}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{[C51, \'a71396, 1397; R60, \'a72427, 2428; C73, \'a72443, 2444; C97, \'a73369; S13, \'a73377; C24, 27, 31, 35, 39, \'a7}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{11994, 12015;}}}{ C46, 50, 54, 58, 62, \'a7636.9, 636.30; C66, 71, 73, 75, 77, 79, }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{81, \'a7633.247}}}{]}\par}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{84 Acts, ch 1080, \'a75}}}{; }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{88 Acts, ch 1064, \'a75}}}{; }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{2005 Acts, ch 38, \'a722}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\keep\keepn\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0\cbpat2{Referred to in }{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{\'a7633.253}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb219\ri0\li0{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\chcbpat2}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{633.248}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E1_30_2E5_2E3_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E1_30_2E5_2E3_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Referee \u8212\'3f notice.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{In the absence of mutual consent of all interested parties to the appointment of referees, the court shall fix a time and place for hearing upon such application and of the fact that referees will be appointed if such application is granted, and shall prescribe the time and manner of the service of notice of the hearing.}\par}{}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{[C51, \'a71398; R60, \'a72429; C73, \'a72445; C97, \'a73370; C24, 27, 31, 35, 39, \'a7}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{11995;}}}{ C46, 50, 54, 58, 62, \'a7636.10; C66, 71, 73, 75, 77, 79, }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{81, \'a7633.248}}}{]}\par}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{2005 Acts, ch 38, \'a723}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\keep\keepn\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0\cbpat2{Referred to in }{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{\'a7633.253}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb219\ri0\li0}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0\cbpat2\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{633.249}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E1_30_2E5_2E4_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E1_30_2E5_2E4_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Mode of setting off share in real estate.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{The referees may employ a licensed professional land surveyor, and may cause the shares in real estate to be set off by legally sufficient land descriptions. They shall make a report of their proceedings to the court as early as reasonably possible.}\par}{}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{[C51, \'a71399; R60, \'a72430; C73, \'a72446; C97, \'a73371; C24, 27, 31, 35, 39, \'a7}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{11996;}}}{ C46, 50, 54, 58, 62, \'a7636.11; C66, 71, 73, 75, 77, 79, }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{81, \'a7633.249}}}{]}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{2012 Acts, ch 1009, \'a733}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\keep\keepn\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0\cbpat2{Referred to in }{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{\'a7633.253}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb219\ri0\li0{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\chcbpat2}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{633.250}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E1_30_2E5_2E5_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E1_30_2E5_2E5_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Report \u8212\'3f delinquency.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{The court may require a report by such a time as it deems reasonable. If the referees fail to obey this or any other of its orders, the court may discharge them and appoint others in their stead, and impose upon the first referees the payment of all costs previously made, unless they show good cause against it.}\par}{}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{[C51, \'a71400; R60, \'a72431; C73, \'a72447; C97, \'a73372; C24, 27, 31, 35, 39, \'a7}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{11997;}}}{ C46, 50, 54, 58, 62, \'a7636.12; C66, 71, 73, 75, 77, 79, }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{81, \'a7633.250}}}{]}\par}{}{\pard\plain\keep\keepn\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0\cbpat2{Referred to in }{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{\'a7633.253}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb219\ri0\li0{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\chcbpat2}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{633.251}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E1_30_2E5_2E6_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E1_30_2E5_2E6_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Confirmation \u8212\'3f new reference.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{The court may set the report for hearing and prescribe the notice to be given to interested parties. The court may confirm the report, or may set it aside and refer the matter to the same or other referees, at its discretion.}\par}{}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{[C51, \'a71401; R60, \'a72432; C73, \'a72448; C97, \'a73373; C24, 27, 31, 35, 39, \'a7}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{11998;}}}{ C46, 50, 54, 58, 62, \'a7636.13; C66, 71, 73, 75, 77, 79, }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{81, \'a7633.251}}}{]}\par}{}{\pard\plain\keep\keepn\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0\cbpat2{Referred to in }{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{\'a7633.253}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb219\ri0\li0{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\chcbpat2}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{633.252}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E1_30_2E5_2E7_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E1_30_2E5_2E7_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Confirmation conclusive \u8212\'3f possession.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{An order confirming a report of the referee shall be binding and conclusive unless appealed within thirty days and the surviving spouse may bring an action to obtain possession of any assets set apart to the surviving spouse. Such elective share constitutes a judgment lien in favor of such surviving spouse against the possessor of such assets.}\par}{}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{[C51, \'a71402; R60, \'a72433; C73, \'a72449; C97, \'a73373; C24, 27, 31, 35, 39, \'a7}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{11999;}}}{ C46, 50, 54, 58, 62, \'a7636.14; C66, 71, 73, 75, 77, 79, }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{81, \'a7633.252}}}{]}\par}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{2005 Acts, ch 38, \'a724}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\keep\keepn\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0\cbpat2{Referred to in }{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{\'a7633.253}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb219\ri0\li0{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\chcbpat2}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{633.253}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E1_30_2E5_2E8_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E1_30_2E5_2E8_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Right contested.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{Nothing in }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{sections 633.247 through 633.252}}}{ shall prevent any person interested from controverting the right of the surviving spouse to the share thus set apart before confirmation of the report of the referees.}\par}{}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{[C51, \'a71403; R60, \'a72434; C73, \'a72450; C97, \'a73374; C24, 27, 31, 35, 39, \'a7}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{12000;}}}{ C46, 50, 54, 58, 62, \'a7636.15; C66, 71, 73, 75, 77, 79, }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{81, \'a7633.253}}}{]}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb219\ri0\li0{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\chcbpat2}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{633.254}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E1_30_2E5_2E9_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E1_30_2E5_2E9_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Sale \u8212\'3f division of proceeds.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{If it appears to the court, upon application of the personal representative, the surviving spouse, or the report of the referee, that the property, or any part of it, cannot be advantageously divided, the court may order the whole, or any part of such property, sold, and the share of the surviving spouse in the proceeds paid over to the surviving spouse.}\par}{}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{[C51, \'a71404; R60, \'a72478; C73, \'a72451; C97, \'a73375; C24, 27, 31, 35, 39, \'a7}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{12001;}}}{ C46, 50, 54, 58, 62, \'a7636.16; C66, 71, 73, 75, 77, 79, }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{81, \'a7633.254}}}{]}\par}{}{\pard\plain\keep\keepn\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0\cbpat2{Referred to in }{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{\'a7633.256}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 633.258}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb219\ri0\li0{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\chcbpat2}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{633.255}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E1_30_2E5_2E1_30_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E1_30_2E5_2E1_30_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Purchase of new homestead.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{In case the homestead is sold, the surviving spouse may use any or all of the spouse\u8217\'3fs share to procure a homestead which shall be exempt from liability for all debts from which the former homestead would have been exempt.}\par}{}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{[C51, \'a71406; C73, \'a72451; C97, \'a73375; C24, 27, 31, 35, 39, \'a7}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{12002;}}}{ C46, 50, 54, 58, 62, \'a7636.17; C66, 71, 73, 75, 77, 79, }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{81, \'a7633.255}}}{]}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb219\ri0\li0{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\chcbpat2}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{633.256}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E1_30_2E5_2E11_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E1_30_2E5_2E11_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Security to avoid sale.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{No sale shall be made under }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 633.254}}}{ if anyone interested gives security to the satisfaction of the court, conditioned to pay the surviving spouse the appraised value of the share with seven percent interest on the same, within such reasonable time as the court may fix, not exceeding one year.}\par}{}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{[C51, \'a71405; C73, \'a72451; C97, \'a73375; C24, 27, 31, 35, 39, \'a7}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{12003;}}}{ C46, 50, 54, 58, 62, \'a7636.18; C66, 71, 73, 75, 77, 79, }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{81, \'a7633.256}}}{]}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb219\ri0\li0{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\chcbpat2}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{633.257}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E1_30_2E5_2E12_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E1_30_2E5_2E12_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Security by surviving spouse.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{If no such arrangement is made, the surviving spouse may keep the property by giving like security to pay the claims of all others interested upon like terms.}\par}{}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{[C51, \'a71405; C73, \'a72451; C97, \'a73375; C24, 27, 31, 35, 39, \'a7}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{12004;}}}{ C46, 50, 54, 58, 62, \'a7636.19; C66, 71, 73, 75, 77, 79, }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{81, \'a7633.257}}}{]}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb219\ri0\li0{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\chcbpat2}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{633.258}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E1_30_2E5_2E13_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E1_30_2E5_2E13_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Sale prohibited.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{Such sale under }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 633.254}}}{ shall not be ordered so long as those in interest shall express a contrary desire and agree upon some mode of sharing and dividing the rents, profits, or use thereof, or shall consent that the court shall order the division of such rents, profits or use.}\par}{}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{[C51, \'a71405; R60, \'a72478; C73, \'a72451; C97, \'a73375; C24, 27, 31, 35, 39, \'a7}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{12005;}}}{ C46, 50, 54, 58, 62, \'a7636.20; C66, 71, 73, 75, 77, 79, }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{81, \'a7633.258}}}{]}\par}{}{\pard\plain\keep\f5\fs18\qj\fi0\sb260\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\qj{633.259 through 633.263}}}{Reserved.}{\f5\fs18\qj\chcbpat2}{\f5\fs18\qj}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\fi0\ri0\li0{\f5\fs18\chcbpat2}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\qc\fi0\sb360\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\qc{SUBCHAPTER VI}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keep\keepn\f5\fs18\qc\fi0\sb120\ri0\li0{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E11_2E2_2E2}{WILLS}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E11_2E2_2E2}\par}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\qc\fi0\sb360\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\qc{PART 1}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keep\keepn\f5\fs18\qc\fi0\sb120\ri0\li0{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E11_2E3_2E1_2E2}{GENERAL PROVISIONS RELATING TO WILLS}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E11_2E3_2E1_2E2}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb360\ri0\li0{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\chcbpat2}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{633.264}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E11_2E3_2E2_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E11_2E3_2E2_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Disposal of property by will.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{Subject to the rights of the surviving spouse to take an elective share as provided by }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 633.236}}}{, any person of full age and sound mind may dispose by will of all the person\u8217\'3fs property, except an amount sufficient to pay the debts and charges against the person\u8217\'3fs estate.}\par}{}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{[C51, \'a71277, 1407; R60, \'a72309, 2435; C73, \'a72322, 2452; C97, \'a73270, 3376; S13, \'a73376; C24, 27, 31, 35, 39, \'a7}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{11846, 12006;}}}{ C46, 50, 54, 58, 62, \'a7633.1, 636.21; C66, 71, 73, 75, 77, 79, }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{81, \'a7633.264}}}{]}\par}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{2005 Acts, ch 38, \'a725}}}{; }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{2006 Acts, ch 1030, \'a777}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\keep\keepn\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0\cbpat2{Referred to in }{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{\'a7726.25}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb219\ri0\li0{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\chcbpat2}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{633.265}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E11_2E3_2E3_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E11_2E3_2E3_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Procedure prescribed by will.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{When the interests of creditors will not thereby be prejudiced, a testator may prescribe the entire manner in which the testator\u8217\'3fs estate shall be administered, and, also, the manner in which the testator\u8217\'3fs affairs shall be conducted until the testator\u8217\'3fs estate is finally settled.}\par}{}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{[C51, \'a71326; R60, \'a72358; C73, \'a72406; C97, \'a73336; C24, 27, 31, 35, 39, \'a7}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{11955;}}}{ C46, 50, 54, 58, 62, \'a7635.51; C66, 71, 73, 75, 77, 79, }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{81, \'a7633.265}}}{]}\par}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj}{For waiver of bond, see }{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{\'a7633.172}}}{ }\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb219\ri0\li0}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0\cbpat2\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{633.266}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E11_2E3_2E4_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E11_2E3_2E4_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Adjusted gross estate.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{Unless otherwise defined, }{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fadjusted gross estate\u8221\'3f}}}{ in a will means the entire value of the gross estate as determined under the federal estate tax less the aggregate amount of the deductions allowed by sections 2053 and 2054 of the Internal Revenue Code as defined in }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 422.3}}}{.}\par}{}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{[}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{82 Acts, ch 1053, \'a71}}}{]}\par}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{2006 Acts, ch 1140, \'a79 \u8211\'3f 11}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\keep\keepn\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0\cbpat2{Referred to in }{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{\'a7633A.1102}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb219\ri0\li0}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0\cbpat2\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{633.267}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E11_2E3_2E5_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E11_2E3_2E5_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Children born or adopted after execution of will.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{1.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{If a testator fails to provide in the testator\u8217\'3fs will for any child of the testator born to or adopted by the testator after the execution of the testator\u8217\'3fs last will, such child, whether born before or after the testator\u8217\'3fs death, shall receive a share in the estate of the testator equal in value to that which the child would have received under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 633.219}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, after taking into account the spouse\u8217\'3fs intestate share under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 633.211}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ or}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ section 633.212}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, whichever section or sections are applicable, if the testator had died intestate, unless it appears from the will that such omission was intentional.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{2.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{a.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{For the purposes of }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{this section}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, a child born after the testator\u8217\'3fs death includes a child of the testator conceived and born after the testator\u8217\'3fs death, or a child born as the result of the implantation of an embryo after the testator\u8217\'3fs death, if all of the following conditions are met:}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{(1)}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{A genetic parent-child relationship between the child and the testator is established. }}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{(2)}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{The testator, in a signed writing, authorized the testator\u8217\'3fs surviving spouse to use the deceased parent\u8217\'3fs genetic material to initiate the posthumous procedure that resulted in the child\u8217\'3fs birth or the testator by specific reference to the genetic material, bequeathed the genetic material to the other parent in a valid will.}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{(3)}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{The child is born within two years of the death of the testator.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{b.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Any child of the testator whose share of the estate would be reduced by the birth of a child born as provided in paragraph }}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fa\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ shall have one year from the birth of the child within which to bring an action challenging the child\u8217\'3fs right to a share of the estate under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{this section}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{c.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{For the purposes of }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{this subsection}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, }}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fgenetic material\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ means sperm, eggs, or embryos.}}}\par}{}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{[C51, \'a71284, 1285; R60, \'a72316, 2317; C73, \'a72334, 2335; C97, \'a73279; S13, \'a73279; C24, 27, 31, 35, 39, \'a7}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{11858;}}}{ C46, 50, 54, 58, 62, \'a7633.13; C66, 71, 73, 75, 77, 79, }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{81, \'a7633.267}}}{]}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{88 Acts, ch 1064, \'a76}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2008 Acts, ch 1119, \'a717, 39}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2011 Acts, ch 18, \'a73}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\keep\keepn\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0\cbpat2{Referred to in }{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{\'a7633.477}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 633A.3106}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb219\ri0\li0{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\chcbpat2}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{633.268}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E11_2E3_2E6_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E11_2E3_2E6_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Presumption attending devise to spouse.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{Where the testator\u8217\'3fs spouse is named as a devisee in a will, it shall be presumed, unless the intent is clear and explicit to the contrary, and except as provided in }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 633.272}}}{, that such devise is in lieu of the intestate share and homestead rights of the surviving spouse.}\par}{}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{[C97, \'a73270; C24, 27, 31, 35, 39, \'a7}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{11847;}}}{ C46, 50, 54, 58, 62, \'a7633.2; C66, 71, 73, 75, 77, 79, }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{81, \'a7633.268}}}{]}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb219\ri0\li0{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\chcbpat2}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{633.269}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E11_2E3_2E7_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E11_2E3_2E7_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{After acquired property.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{Any property acquired by the testator after the making of the testator\u8217\'3fs will shall pass thereby, and in like manner as if title thereto were vested in the testator at the time of making the will, unless the intent is clear and explicit to the contrary.}\par}{}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{[C51, \'a71278; R60, \'a72310; C73, \'a72323; C97, \'a73271; C24, 27, 31, 35, 39, \'a7}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{11849;}}}{ C46, 50, 54, 58, 62, \'a7633.4; C66, 71, 73, 75, 77, 79, }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{81, \'a7633.269}}}{]}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb219\ri0\li0{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\chcbpat2}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{633.270}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E11_2E3_2E8_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E11_2E3_2E8_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Contractual or mutual wills.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{No will shall be construed to be contractual or mutual, unless in such will the testator shall expressly state the intent that such will shall be so construed.}\par}{}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{[C66, 71, 73, 75, 77, 79, }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{81, \'a7633.270}}}{]}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb219\ri0\li0{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\chcbpat2}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{633.271}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E11_2E3_2E9_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E11_2E3_2E9_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Effect of divorce or dissolution.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{1.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{If after making a will the testator is divorced or the testator\u8217\'3fs marriage is dissolved, all provisions in the will in favor of the testator\u8217\'3fs spouse or of a relative of the testator\u8217\'3fs spouse, including but not limited to dispositions, appointments of property, and nominations to serve in any fiduciary or representative capacity, are revoked by the divorce or dissolution of marriage, unless the will provides otherwise.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{2.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Unless the will provides otherwise, in the event the testator and spouse remarry each other, the provisions of the will revoked by the divorce or dissolution of marriage shall be reinstated unless otherwise revoked by the testator, except for provisions in favor of a person who died prior to the remarriage which shall not be reinstated.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{3.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{For the purposes of }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{this section}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, }}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3frelative of the testator\u8217\'3fs spouse\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ means a person who is related to the divorced testator\u8217\'3fs former spouse by blood, adoption, or affinity, and who, subsequent to a divorce or dissolution of marriage, ceased to be related to the testator by blood, adoption, or affinity.}}}\par}{}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{[C66, 71, 73, 75, 77, 79, }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{81, \'a7633.271}}}{]}\par}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{2000 Acts, ch 1150, \'a73}}}{; }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{2005 Acts, ch 38, \'a726}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb219\ri0\li0}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0\cbpat2\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{633.272}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E11_2E3_2E1_30_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E11_2E3_2E1_30_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Partial intestacy.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{If part but not all of the estate of a decedent is validly disposed of by will, the part not disposed of by will shall be distributed as provided herein for intestate estates. If the testator left a surviving spouse, and the spouse does not take an elective share, the spouse shall receive, in addition to the property given to the spouse by the will, so much of the intestate property subject to the payment of its proportionate share of debts and charges as the spouse would receive pursuant to }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 633.211}}}{ or }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{633.212}}}{.}\par}{}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{[C66, 71, 73, 75, 77, 79, }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{81, \'a7633.272}}}{]}\par}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{94 Acts, ch 1165, \'a742}}}{; }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{2007 Acts, ch 134, \'a712, 28}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\keep\keepn\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0\cbpat2{Referred to in }{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{\'a7633.268}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb219\ri0\li0{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\chcbpat2}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{633.273}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E11_2E3_2E11_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E11_2E3_2E11_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Antilapse statute.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{1.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{If a devisee dies before the testator, leaving issue who survive the testator, the devisee\u8217\'3fs issue who survive the testator shall inherit the property devised to the devisee per stirpes, unless from the terms of the will, the intent is clear and explicit to the contrary.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{2.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{A person who would have been a devisee under a class gift, if the person had survived the testator, is treated as a devisee for purposes of }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{this section}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, provided the person\u8217\'3fs death occurred after the execution of the will, unless from the terms of the will, the intent is clear and explicit to the contrary.}}}\par}{}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{[C51, \'a71287; R60, \'a72319; C73, \'a72337; C97, \'a73281; C24, 27, 31, 35, 39, \'a7}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{11861;}}}{ C46, 50, 54, 58, 62, \'a7633.16; C66, 71, 73, 75, 77, 79, }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{81, \'a7633.273}}}{]}\par}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{89 Acts, ch 130, \'a71}}}{; }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{95 Acts, ch 63, \'a75}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\keep\keepn\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0\cbpat2{Referred to in }{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{\'a7633.273A}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 633.274}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb219\ri0\li0}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0\cbpat2\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{633.273A}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E11_2E3_2E12_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E11_2E3_2E12_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Disposition of failed devise.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{Unless from the terms of the will the intent is clear and explicit to the contrary, and except as provided in }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 633.273}}}{:}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{1.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{A devise, other than a residuary devise, that fails for any reason becomes a part of the residuary estate.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{2.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{If the residuary estate is devised to two or more persons, the share of a residuary devisee that fails for any reason passes to the other residuary devisee or to the other residuary devisees in proportion to the interest of each in the remaining part of the residuary estate.}}}\par}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{2013 Acts, ch 33, \'a71, 9}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb219\ri0\li0{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\chcbpat2}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{633.274}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E11_2E3_2E13_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E11_2E3_2E13_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Exception to antilapse statute.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{The devise to a spouse of the testator, where the spouse does not survive the testator, shall lapse notwithstanding the provisions of }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 633.273}}}{, unless from the terms of the will, the intent is clear and explicit to the contrary.}\par}{}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{[C66, 71, 73, 75, 77, 79, }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{81, \'a7633.274}}}{]}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb219\ri0\li0{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\chcbpat2}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{633.275}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E11_2E3_2E14_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E11_2E3_2E14_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Testamentary additions to trusts.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{A devise or bequest, the validity of which is determinable by the law of this state, may be made by a will to the trustee of a trust established, or to be established, by the testator, or by the testator and some other person or persons, or by some other person or persons, including a funded or unfunded life insurance trust, although the trustor has reserved some or all rights of ownership of the insurance contracts, if the trust is identified in the testator\u8217\'3fs will, and if its terms are set forth in a written instrument other than a will executed before or concurrently with the execution of the testator\u8217\'3fs will, or in the valid last will of a person who has predeceased the testator regardless of the existence, size, or character of the corpus of the trust. The devise or bequest is not invalid because the trust is amendable or revocable, or both, or because the trust was amended after the execution of the will or after the death of the testator. Unless the testator\u8217\'3fs will provides otherwise, the property so devised or bequeathed shall not be deemed to be held under a testamentary trust of the testator, but shall become a part of the trust to which it is given and shall be administered and disposed of in accordance with the instrument or will setting forth the terms of the trust, including any amendments thereto made before the death of the testator, regardless of whether any such amendment was made before or after the execution of the testator\u8217\'3fs will, and, if the testator\u8217\'3fs will so provides, including any amendments to the trust made after the death of the testator. A revocation or termination of the trust before the death of the testator causes the devise or bequest to lapse. }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{This section}}}{ does not invalidate a devise or bequest made by a will executed prior to January 1, 1964.}\par}{}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{[C66, 71, 73, 75, 77, 79, }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{81, \'a7633.275}}}{, }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{633.276}}}{; }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{81 Acts, ch 195, \'a71}}}{]}\par}{}{\pard\plain\keep\keepn\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0\cbpat2{Referred to in }{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{\'a7633.277}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb219\ri0\li0{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\chcbpat2}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{633.276}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E11_2E3_2E15_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E11_2E3_2E15_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Separate identification of bequest.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{A will may refer to a written statement, letter, or list to dispose of items of tangible personal property not otherwise specifically disposed of by the will, except tangible personal property used in trade or business. Tangible personal property, for purposes of }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{this section}}}{, includes household goods, furnishings, furniture, personal effects, clothing, jewelry, books, works of art, ornaments, and automobiles. If the writing is dated and is either in the handwriting of the testator or is signed by testator, and if it describes the items and distributees with reasonable certainty, the personal representative shall distribute the described items of tangible personal property to the distributees entitled to them. The writing may be referred to as one to be in existence at the time of the testator\u8217\'3fs death. The writing may be prepared before or after the execution of the will. The writing may be altered, added to, or changed in any respect by the testator after its preparation, and it may be a writing which has no significance apart from its effect upon the dispositions made by the will. Property passing by the writing shall be considered as property passing as a specific bequest under will.}\par}{}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{[}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{81 Acts, ch 195, \'a72}}}{]}\par}{}{\pard\plain\keep\keepn\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0\cbpat2{Referred to in }{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{\'a7450.4}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb219\ri0\li0{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\chcbpat2}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{633.277}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E11_2E3_2E16_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E11_2E3_2E16_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Uniformity of interpretation.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Section 633.275}}}{ shall be so construed as to effectuate its general purpose to make uniform the law of those states which have adopted a similar provision.}\par}{}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{[C66, 71, 73, 75, 77, 79, }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{81, \'a7633.277}}}{]}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb219\ri0\li0{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\chcbpat2}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{633.278}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E11_2E3_2E17_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E11_2E3_2E17_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Devise of encumbered property.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{When any property subject to a mortgage, other lien or security interest, is specifically devised, the devisee shall take such property so devised subject to such mortgage, other lien or security interest, unless the will provides expressly or by necessary implication that such mortgage, other lien or security interest be otherwise paid. If there is a testamentary direction to discharge such mortgage, other lien or security interest, the rules of abatement specified in }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 633.436}}}{ shall be applied.}\par}{}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{[C66, 71, 73, 75, 77, 79, }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{81, \'a7633.278}}}{]}\par}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\qc\fi0\sb360\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\qc{PART 2}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keep\keepn\f5\fs18\qc\fi0\sb120\ri0\li0{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E11_2E4_2E1_2E2}{EXECUTION AND REVOCATION}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E11_2E4_2E1_2E2}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb360\ri0\li0}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0\cbpat2\par}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0\cbpat2\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{633.279}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E11_2E4_2E2_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E11_2E4_2E2_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Signed and witnessed.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{1.}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E11_2E4_2E2_2E3_2E1_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E11_2E4_2E2_2E3_2E1_2E2}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Formal execution.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{All wills and codicils, except as provided in }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 633.283}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, to be valid, must be in writing, signed by the testator, or by some person in the testator\u8217\'3fs presence and by the testator\u8217\'3fs express direction writing the testator\u8217\'3fs name thereto, and declared by the testator to be the testator\u8217\'3fs will, and witnessed, at the testator\u8217\'3fs request, by two competent persons who signed as witnesses in the presence of the testator and in the presence of each other; provided, however, that the validity of the execution of any will or instrument which was executed prior to January 1, 1964, shall be determined by the law in effect immediately prior to said date.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{2.}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E11_2E4_2E2_2E4_2E1_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E11_2E4_2E2_2E4_2E1_2E2}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Self-proved will.}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{a.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{An attested will may be made self-proved at the time of its execution, or at any subsequent date, by the acknowledgment thereof by the testator and the affidavits of the witnesses, each made before a person authorized to administer oaths and take acknowledgments under the laws of this state, and evidenced by such person\u8217\'3fs certificate, under seal, attached or annexed to the will, in form and content substantially as follows:}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qc\fi0\ri1084\li1084{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qc}{Affidavit}{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qc}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084{State of}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{........................}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~}}}{)}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084\sa0\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084{County of}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{........................}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~}}}{)}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{ss}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084\sa0\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{We, the undersigned, }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{............................}}}{, }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{............................}}}{ and }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{....................................}}}{, the testator and the witnesses, respectively, whose names are signed to the attached or foregoing instrument, being first duly sworn, declare to the undersigned authority that at the date of the instrument, we all knew the identity of each other; the instrument was exhibited to the witnesses by the testator, who declared it to be the testator\u8217\'3fs last will and testament and was signed by the testator or by another at the direction of the testator at }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{................................}}}{, in the County of }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{........................}}}{, State of }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{........................}}}{, on the date shown in the instrument, and in the presence of each other as subscribing witnesses; that we, as witnesses, declare to the undersigned authority that in our presence the testator executed and acknowledged such will as the testator\u8217\'3fs will and that we, in the testator\u8217\'3fs presence, at the testator\u8217\'3fs request, and in the presence of each other, did subscribe our names thereto as attesting witnesses on the date of such will; and that the witnesses were sixteen years of age or older.}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084\sa0\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084{............................}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084\sa0\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084{Testator}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084\sa0\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084{............................}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084\sa0\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084{Witness}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084\sa0\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084{............................}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084\sa0\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084{Witness}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084\sa0\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084{............................}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084\sa0\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{Subscribed, sworn and acknowledged before me by }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{................................}}}{, the testator; and subscribed and sworn before me by }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{................................}}}{ and }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{............................}}}{, witnesses, this }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{............}}}{ day of }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{........................}}}{ (month), }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{............}}}{ (year)}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084\sa0\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~}}}{.............................}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084\sa0\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084\sa0\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~}}}{Signature of notarial}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084\sa0\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~}}}{officer }\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084\sa0\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084{(Stamp)}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084\sa0\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084\sa0\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~}}}{[...................]}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084\sa0\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~}}}{Title of office}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084\sa0\par}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084\sa80{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~}}}{[My commission expires]}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{b.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{A self-proved will shall constitute proof of due execution of such instrument as required by }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 633.293}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ and may be admitted to probate without testimony of witnesses.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{3.}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E11_2E4_2E2_2E5_2E1_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E11_2E4_2E2_2E5_2E1_2E2}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Execution of remote will or codicil in counterparts.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{When a will or codicil is executed using remote signing under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{this section}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, the original document may be executed in one or more counterparts by parties located in different locations, and all such counterparts may be aggregated to comprise the complete will or codicil of the testator.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{4.}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E11_2E4_2E2_2E6_2E1_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E11_2E4_2E2_2E6_2E1_2E2}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Remote will or codicil under disaster proclamation.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Any will or codicil executed using the remote signing procedures permitted under the proclamation of disaster emergency of the governor issued April 2, 2020, and expired February 15, 2022, shall be deemed to satisfy the presence requirements of }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{this section}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ if the will or codicil was executed during the effective period of the proclamation of disaster emergency.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{5.}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E11_2E4_2E2_2E7_2E1_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E11_2E4_2E2_2E7_2E1_2E2}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Definition.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{For purposes of }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{this section}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, }}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fpresence\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ means any manner, physical or electronic, in which the witness and testator can see and hear the acts of each other in real time.}}}\par}{}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{[C51, \'a71281; R60, \'a72313; C73, \'a72326; C97, \'a73274; C24, 27, 31, 35, 39, \'a7}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{11852;}}}{ C46, 50, 54, 58, 62, \'a7633.7; C66, 71, 73, 75, 77, 79, }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{81, \'a7633.279}}}{]}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{2000 Acts, ch 1058, \'a756}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2011 Acts, ch 25, \'a773}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2012 Acts, ch 1050, \'a757, 60}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2013 Acts, ch 33, \'a72, 9}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2015 Acts, ch 30, \'a7180}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2023 Acts, ch 133, \'a72, 3}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\keep\keepn\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0\cbpat2{Referred to in }{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{\'a7622.1}}}\par}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj}{Subsection 4 applies retroactively to wills and codicils executed on or after April 2, 2020; }{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{2023 Acts, ch 133, \'a73}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb219\ri0\li0{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\chcbpat2}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{633.280}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E11_2E4_2E3_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E11_2E4_2E3_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Competency of witnesses.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{Any person who is sixteen years of age, or older, and who is competent to be a witness generally in this state, may act as an attesting witness to a will.}\par}{}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{[C66, 71, 73, 75, 77, 79, }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{81, \'a7633.280}}}{]}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb219\ri0\li0{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\chcbpat2}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{633.281}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E11_2E4_2E4_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E11_2E4_2E4_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Interest of witnesses.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{No will is invalidated because attested by an interested witness; but any interested witness shall, unless the will is also attested by two competent and disinterested witnesses, forfeit so much of the provisions therein made for the interested witness as in the aggregate exceeds in value, as of the date of the decedent\u8217\'3fs death, that which the interested witness would have received had the testator died intestate. No attesting witness is interested unless the witness is devised or bequeathed some portion of the testator\u8217\'3fs estate.}\par}{}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{[C51, \'a71282, 1283; R60, \'a72314, 2315; C73, \'a72327, 2328; C97, \'a73275; C24, 27, 31, 35, 39, \'a7}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{11854;}}}{ C46, 50, 54, 58, 62, \'a7633.9; C66, 71, 73, 75, 77, 79, }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{81, \'a7633.281}}}{]}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb219\ri0\li0{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\chcbpat2}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{633.282}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E11_2E4_2E5_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E11_2E4_2E5_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Defect cured by codicil.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{If a codicil to a defectively executed will is duly executed, and such will is clearly identified in said codicil, the will and the codicil shall be considered as one instrument and the execution of both shall be deemed sufficient.}\par}{}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{[C97, \'a73274; C24, 27, 31, 35, 39, \'a7}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{11853;}}}{ C46, 50, 54, 58, 62, \'a7633.8; C66, 71, 73, 75, 77, 79, }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{81, \'a7633.282}}}{]}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb219\ri0\li0{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\chcbpat2}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{633.283}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E11_2E4_2E6_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E11_2E4_2E6_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Will executed in foreign state or country.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{A will executed outside this state, in the mode prescribed by the law, either of the place where executed or of the testator\u8217\'3fs domicile, shall be deemed to be legally executed, and shall be of the same force and effect as if executed in the mode prescribed by the laws of this state, provided said will is in writing and subscribed by the testator.}\par}{}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{[C97, \'a73309; C24, 27, 31, 35, 39, \'a7}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{11893;}}}{ C46, 50, 54, 58, 62, \'a7633.49; C66, 71, 73, 75, 77, 79, }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{81, \'a7633.283}}}{]}\par}{}{\pard\plain\keep\keepn\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0\cbpat2{Referred to in }{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{\'a7633.279}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb219\ri0\li0{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\chcbpat2}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{633.284}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E11_2E4_2E7_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E11_2E4_2E7_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Revocation \u8212\'3f cancellation \u8212\'3f revival.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{A will can be revoked in whole or in part only by being canceled or destroyed by the act or direction of the testator, with the intention of revoking it, or by the execution of a subsequent will. When done by cancellation, the revocation must be witnessed in the same manner as the making of a new will. No will, nor any part thereof, which shall be in any manner revoked, or which shall be or become invalid, can be revived otherwise than by a re-execution thereof, or by the execution of another will or codicil in which the revoked or invalid will, or part thereof, is incorporated by reference.}\par}{}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{[C51, \'a71288, 1289; R60, \'a72320, 2321; C73, \'a72329, 2330; C97, \'a73276; S13, \'a73276; C24, 27, 31, 35, 39, \'a7}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{11855;}}}{ C46, 50, 54, 58, 62, \'a7633.10; C66, 71, 73, 75, 77, 79, }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{81, \'a7633.284}}}{]}\par}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\qc\fi0\sb360\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\qc{PART 3}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keep\keepn\f5\fs18\qc\fi0\sb120\ri0\li0{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E11_2E5_2E1_2E2}{CUSTODY}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E11_2E5_2E1_2E2}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb360\ri0\li0{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\chcbpat2}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{633.285}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E11_2E5_2E2_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E11_2E5_2E2_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Custodian \u8212\'3f filing \u8212\'3f penalty.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{After being informed of the death of the testator, the person having custody of the testator\u8217\'3fs will shall deliver it to the court having jurisdiction of the testator\u8217\'3fs estate. Every person who willfully refuses or fails to deliver a will after being ordered by the court to do so shall be guilty of contempt of court. The person shall also be liable to any person aggrieved for the damages which may be sustained by such refusal or failure.}\par}{}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{[C51, \'a71291, 1292; R60, \'a72323, 2324; C73, \'a72338, 2339; C97, \'a73282; C24, 27, 31, 35, 39, \'a7}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{11862;}}}{ C46, 50, 54, 58, 62, \'a7633.17; C66, 71, 73, 75, 77, 79, }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{81, \'a7633.285}}}{]}\par}{}{\pard\plain\keep\keepn\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0\cbpat2{Referred to in }{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{\'a7633.286}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb219\ri0\li0{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\chcbpat2}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{633.286}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E11_2E5_2E3_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E11_2E5_2E3_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Deposit of will with clerk.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{The clerk shall maintain a file for the safekeeping of wills. There shall be placed therein wills deposited with the clerk by living testators or by persons on their behalf, and wills of deceased testators not accompanied by petitions for the probate thereof, when deposited with the clerk by persons having custody thereof as provided in }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 633.285}}}{.}\par}{}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{[C51, \'a71290; R60, \'a72322; C73, \'a72331; C97, \'a73277; C24, 27, 31, 35, 39, \'a7}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{11856;}}}{ C46, 50, 54, 58, 62, \'a7633.11; C66, 71, 73, 75, 77, 79, }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{81, \'a7633.286}}}{]}\par}{}{\pard\plain\keep\keepn\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0\cbpat2{Referred to in }{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{\'a7633.645}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb219\ri0\li0{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\chcbpat2}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{633.287}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E11_2E5_2E4_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E11_2E5_2E4_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Manner of deposit.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{Every such will shall be enclosed in a sealed wrapper. The clerk shall indorse thereon the name of the testator, the name of the depositor, the date of deposit, and, if provided, the name of the person to be notified of the deposit of such will upon the death of the testator. The clerk shall hold such will until disposed of as provided in }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 633.288}}}{ or }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{633.289}}}{.}\par}{}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{[C66, 71, 73, 75, 77, 79, }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{81, \'a7633.287}}}{]}\par}{}{\pard\plain\keep\keepn\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0\cbpat2{Referred to in }{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{\'a7633.645}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb219\ri0\li0{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\chcbpat2}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{633.288}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E11_2E5_2E5_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E11_2E5_2E5_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Delivery by clerk during lifetime of testator.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{During the lifetime of the testator, such will shall be delivered only to the testator, or to some person authorized by the testator by an order in writing duly acknowledged.}\par}{}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{[C66, 71, 73, 75, 77, 79, }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{81, \'a7633.288}}}{]}\par}{}{\pard\plain\keep\keepn\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0\cbpat2{Referred to in }{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{\'a7633.287}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 633.645}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb219\ri0\li0}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0\cbpat2\par}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0\cbpat2\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{633.289}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E11_2E5_2E6_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E11_2E5_2E6_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Delivery by clerk after death of testator.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{After being informed of the death of a testator, the clerk shall notify the person, if any, named in the indorsement on the wrapper of said will. If no petition for the probate thereof has been filed within thirty days after the death of the testator, it shall be publicly opened, and the court shall make such orders as it deems appropriate for the disposition of said will. The clerk shall notify the executor named therein and such other persons as the court shall designate of such action. If the proper venue is in another court, the clerk, upon request, shall transmit such will to such court, but before such transmission, the clerk shall make a true copy thereof and retain the same in the clerk\u8217\'3fs files.}\par}{}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{[C66, 71, 73, 75, 77, 79, }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{81, \'a7633.289}}}{]}\par}{}{\pard\plain\keep\keepn\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0\cbpat2{Referred to in }{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{\'a7633.287}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 633.645}}}\par}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\qc\fi0\sb360\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\qc{PART 4}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keep\keepn\f5\fs18\qc\fi0\sb120\ri0\li0{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E11_2E6_2E1_2E2}{PROCEDURE FOR PROBATE OF WILLS}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E11_2E6_2E1_2E2}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb360\ri0\li0}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0\cbpat2\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{633.290}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E11_2E6_2E2_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E11_2E6_2E2_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ Petitions after death of testator.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{1.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ After the death of the testator, any interested person may file a verified petition in the district court of the proper county for any of the following:}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{a.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{To have the will admitted to probate.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{b.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{For the appointment of the executor.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{c.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{To request a hearing before the will is admitted to probate.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{d.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{To request a hearing before the appointment of the executor.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{e.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{For the production of the purported will of the decedent to be filed by the person believed by the petitioner to be in possession of the will.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{2.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ Petitions for any of the reasons specified in }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{subsection 1}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ may be combined.}}}\par}{}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{[C66, 71, 73, 75, 77, 79, }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{81, \'a7633.290}}}{]}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{2013 Acts, ch 30, \'a7192}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2013 Acts, ch 33, \'a73, 9}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\keep\keepn\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0\cbpat2{Referred to in }{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{\'a7635.1}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb219\ri0\li0{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\chcbpat2}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{633.291}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E11_2E6_2E3_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E11_2E6_2E3_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Contents of petition for probate of will.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{A petition for probate of a will shall state:}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{1.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{The name, domicile, and date of death of the decedent.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{2.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{If the decedent was not domiciled in the state at the time of the decedent\u8217\'3fs death, then, that the decedent had property within the county in which the petition is filed, or any other basis for jurisdiction in such county.}}}\par}{}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{[C66, 71, 73, 75, 77, 79, }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{81, \'a7633.291}}}{]}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb219\ri0\li0{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\chcbpat2}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{633.292}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E11_2E6_2E4_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E11_2E6_2E4_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Contents of petition for appointment of executor.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{A petition for the appointment of an executor shall state the name and address of the person nominated or proposed as executor, and that such person is qualified to act as executor. If the person proposed in said petition is not the person nominated in the will, the petition shall state the reason why the person nominated is not proposed as executor. Unless bond is waived in the will, the petition shall state the estimated value of the personal property of the estate plus the estimated gross annual income of the estate during the period of administration.}\par}{}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{[C66, 71, 73, 75, 77, 79, }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{81, \'a7633.292}}}{]}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb219\ri0\li0{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\chcbpat2}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{633.293}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E11_2E6_2E5_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E11_2E6_2E5_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Hearing upon petition.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{Upon the filing of a petition for probate of a will, the court or the clerk may, in its or the clerk\u8217\'3fs discretion, hear it forthwith, or at such time and place as the court or clerk may direct, with or without requiring notice, and upon proof of due execution of the will, admit the same to probate.}\par}{}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{[C51, \'a71294; R60, \'a72326; C73, \'a72341; C97, \'a73284; S13, \'a73284; C24, 27, 31, 35, 39, \'a7}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{11865;}}}{ C46, 50, 54, 58, 62, \'a7633.20; C66, 71, 73, 75, 77, 79, }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{81, \'a7633.293}}}{]}\par}{}{\pard\plain\keep\keepn\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0\cbpat2{Referred to in }{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{\'a7633.279}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb219\ri0\li0{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\chcbpat2}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{633.294}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E11_2E6_2E6_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E11_2E6_2E6_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Order of preference for appointment of executor.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{Letters testamentary may be granted to one or more persons found to be qualified. Preference for appointment shall be in the following order:}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{1.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{The person designated in the will;}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{2.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Any beneficiary named in the will, or a person nominated by the beneficiaries;}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{3.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Any creditor of the deceased, or a person nominated by such creditor;}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{4.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Such other person as the court may find to be qualified.}}}\par}{}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{[C66, 71, 73, 75, 77, 79, }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{81, \'a7633.294}}}{]}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb219\ri0\li0}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0\cbpat2\par}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0\cbpat2\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{633.295}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E11_2E6_2E7_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E11_2E6_2E7_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Testimony of witnesses.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{The proof may be made by the oral or written testimony of one or more of the subscribing witnesses to the will. If such testimony is in writing, it shall be substantially in the following form executed and sworn to before or after the death of the decedent:}\par}{}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qc\fi0\ri1084\li1084{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qc}{In the District Court of Iowa}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qc\fi0\ri1084\li1084\sa0\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qc\fi0\ri1084\li1084{in and for }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qc{....................}}}{ County.}{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qc}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{In the Matter of}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~}}}{Probate No. }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{................}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084\sa0\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{the Estate of}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~}}}{TESTIMONY OF SUBSCRIBING}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084\sa0\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{........................}}}{, Deceased}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~}}}{WITNESS ON}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084\sa0\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{State of }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{............}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{)}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~}}}{PROBATE OF WILL}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084\sa0\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{............}}}{ County}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{)}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{ss}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084\sa0\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{I, }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{........................}}}{, being first duly sworn, state:}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084\sa0\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{I reside in the County of }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{....................}}}{, State of }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{................}}}{; I knew the identity of the testator on the }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{........}}}{ day of }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{............}}}{ (month), }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{............}}}{ (year), the date of the instrument, the original or exact reproduction of which is attached hereto, now shown to me, and purporting to be the last will and testament of the said }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{........................}}}{; I am one of the subscribing witnesses to said instrument; at the said date of said instrument, I knew the identity of }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{........................}}}{, the other subscribing witness; that said instrument was exhibited to me and to the other subscribing witness by the testator, who declared the same to be the testator\u8217\'3fs last will and testament, and was signed by the testator at }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{................................}}}{, in the County of }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{....................}}}{, State of }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{................}}}{, on the date shown in said instrument, in the presence of myself and the other subscribing witness; and the other subscribing witness and I then and there, at the request of the testator, in the presence of said testator and in the presence of each other, subscribed our names thereto as witnesses.}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084\sa0\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{........................}}}{ }\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084\sa0\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084{Name of Witness}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084\sa0\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{................................}}}{ }\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084\sa0\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084{Address}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084\sa0\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{Subscribed and sworn to before me this }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{........}}}{ day of }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{............}}}{ (month), }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{............}}}{ (year)}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084\sa0\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{................................}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084\sa0\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~}}}{Signature of notarial officer}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084\sa0\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084{(Stamp)}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084\sa0\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~}}}{[}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{........................}}}{]}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084\sa0\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~}}}{Title of office}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084\sa0\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~}}}{[My commission expires: }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{........}}}{]}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084\sa0\par}{\pard\plain\f5\fs8\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084\par}{}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{[C66, 71, 73, 75, 77, 79, }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{81, \'a7633.295}}}{]}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{2000 Acts, ch 1058, \'a756}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2012 Acts, ch 1050, \'a758, 60}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2013 Acts, ch 33, \'a74, 9}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2014 Acts, ch 1021, \'a71, 4 \u8211\'3f 6}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2016 Acts, ch 1073, \'a7172}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\keep\keepn\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0\cbpat2{Referred to in }{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{\'a7633.296}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 633.319}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb219\ri0\li0{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\chcbpat2}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{633.296}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E11_2E6_2E8_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E11_2E6_2E8_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Deposition.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{If it is desired to prove the execution of the will by deposition, rather than by use of the affidavit form provided in }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 633.295}}}{, upon application, the clerk shall issue a commission to some officer authorized by the law of this state to take depositions, with the will annexed, and the officer taking the deposition shall exhibit it to the witness for identification, and, when identified by the witness, shall mark it as \u8220\'3fExhibit }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{............}}}{\u8221\'3f and cause the witness to connect the witness\u8217\'3f identification with it as such exhibit. Before sending out the commission, the clerk shall make and retain in the clerk\u8217\'3fs office a true copy of such will.}\par}{}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{[C97, \'a73285; C24, 27, 31, 35, 39, \'a7}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{11866;}}}{ C46, 50, 54, 58, 62, \'a7633.21; C66, 71, 73, 75, 77, 79, }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{81, \'a7633.296}}}{]}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb219\ri0\li0{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\chcbpat2}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{633.297}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E11_2E6_2E9_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E11_2E6_2E9_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Witnesses unavailable.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{If all of such witnesses are deceased or otherwise not available, then it shall be permissible to prove said will by the sworn testimony of two credible disinterested witnesses that the signature to the will is in the handwriting of the person whose will it purports to be, and that the signatures of the witnesses are in the handwriting of such witnesses, or it may be proved by other sufficient evidence of the execution of such will.}\par}{}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{[C46, 50, 54, 58, 62, \'a7633.22; C66, 71, 73, 75, 77, 79, }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{81, \'a7633.297}}}{]}\par}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj}{Other evidence, proof, }{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{\'a7622.24}}}{ }\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb219\ri0\li0{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\chcbpat2}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{633.298}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E11_2E6_2E1_30_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E11_2E6_2E1_30_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Order admitting or disallowing probate of will.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{The court or the clerk shall enter an order either admitting said will to probate, or disallowing probate because of insufficient proof thereof.}\par}{}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{[C66, 71, 73, 75, 77, 79, }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{81, \'a7633.298}}}{]}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb219\ri0\li0{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\chcbpat2}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{633.299}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E11_2E6_2E11_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E11_2E6_2E11_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Order appointing executor.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{If a petition for appointment of an executor has been filed, the order admitting the will to probate shall include appointment of an executor thereof, unless the court or clerk shall determine that no appointment should be made at such time.}\par}{}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{[C51, \'a71299, 1302; R60, \'a72331, 2334; C73, \'a72332, 2333; C97, \'a73278; C24, 27, 31, 35, 39, \'a7}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{11857;}}}{ C46, 50, 54, 58, 62, \'a7633.12; C66, 71, 73, 75, 77, 79, }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{81, \'a7633.299}}}{]}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb219\ri0\li0{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\chcbpat2}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{633.300}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E11_2E6_2E12_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E11_2E6_2E12_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Certificate of probate.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{When a will has been admitted to probate the clerk shall have a certificate of such fact, endorsed thereon or annexed thereto, signed by the clerk and attested by the seal of the court; and, when so certified, it, or the transcript of the record properly authenticated, may be read in evidence in all courts without further proof.}\par}{}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{[C51, \'a71300; R60, \'a72332; C73, \'a72342; C97, \'a73286; C24, 27, 31, 35, 39, \'a7}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{11867;}}}{ C46, 50, 54, 58, 62, \'a7633.23; C66, 71, 73, 75, 77, 79, }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{81, \'a7633.300}}}{]}\par}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{93 Acts, ch 70, \'a713}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\keep\keepn\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0\cbpat2{Referred to in }{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{\'a7633.301}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb219\ri0\li0}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0\cbpat2\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{633.301}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E11_2E6_2E13_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E11_2E6_2E13_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Copy of will for executor.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{Upon request by the executor, when a will has been admitted to probate and certified pursuant to }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 633.300}}}{, the clerk shall cause a certified copy thereof to be placed in the hands of the executor to whom letters are issued. The clerk shall retain the will in a separate file provided for that purpose until the time for contest has expired, and promptly thereafter shall place it with the files of the estate.}\par}{}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{[C51, \'a71295, 1298; R60, \'a72327, 2330; C73, \'a72343, 2344; C97, \'a73287; S13, \'a73287; C24, 27, 31, 35, 39, \'a7}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{11868;}}}{ C46, 50, 54, 58, 62, \'a7633.24; C66, 71, 73, 75, 77, 79, }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{81, \'a7633.301}}}{]}\par}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{93 Acts, ch 70, \'a714}}}{; }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{2003 Acts, ch 151, \'a753}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2023 Acts, ch 124, \'a73}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\keep\keepn\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0\cbpat2{Referred to in }{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{\'a7633.302}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb219\ri0\li0{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\chcbpat2}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{633.302}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E11_2E6_2E14_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E11_2E6_2E14_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Clerk filing copies of will.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{When the clerk places an original will in a separate file as provided in }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 633.301}}}{, the clerk shall place and keep a true copy of such will in the probate file containing the proceedings in the estate which it governs.}\par}{}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{[C66, 71, 73, 75, 77, 79, }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{81, \'a7633.302}}}{]}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb219\ri0\li0}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0\cbpat2\par}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0\cbpat2\par}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{633.303}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E11_2E6_2E15_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E11_2E6_2E15_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Charitable trusts \u8212\'3f copy of wills to attorney general.}}}{\f5\b\fs2\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Repealed by }}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0\cf5{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\cf5{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://www.legis.iowa.gov/docs/acts/2009/CH0035.pdf" }{\fldrslt \cf5 \f5 \fs18{{2009 Acts, ch 35, \'a73}}}}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{See }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\'a7633A.5107}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ and }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{633A.5108}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{. }}}{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\chcbpat2}{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb219\ri0\li0}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0\cbpat2\par}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0\cbpat2\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{633.304}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E11_2E6_2E16_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E11_2E6_2E16_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Notice of probate of will with administration.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{1.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{As used in }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{this section}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, }}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fheir\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ means only such person as would, in an intestate estate, be entitled to a share under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 633.219}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{2.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{On admission of a will to probate, the executor, as soon as letters are issued, shall cause notice to be published once each week for two consecutive weeks in a daily or weekly newspaper of general circulation published in the county in which the estate is pending. At any time during the pendency of administration that the executor has knowledge of the name and address of a person believed to own or possess a claim which will not or may not be paid or otherwise satisfied during administration, the executor shall provide notice by ordinary mail to each such claimant at the claimant\u8217\'3fs last known address. The executor shall also, as soon as practicable give notice, except to any executor, by ordinary mail to the surviving spouse, each heir of the decedent, and each devisee under the will admitted to probate whose identities are reasonably ascertainable, at such persons\u8217\'3f last known addresses, of admission of the will to probate and of the appointment of the executor. In the notice shall be included a notice that any action to set aside the probate of the will must be brought within the later to occur of four months from the date of the second publication of the notice or one month from the date of mailing of this notice or thereafter be forever barred, a notice to debtors to make payment, and a notice to creditors having claims against the estate to file them with the clerk within four months from the second publication of the notice, or thereafter be forever barred.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{3.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{The notice shall be substantially in the following form:}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qc\fi0\ri1084\li1084{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qc}{In the District Court of Iowa}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qc\fi0\ri1084\li1084\sa0\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qc\fi0\ri1084\li1084{in and for }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qc{....................}}}{ County.}{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qc}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~}}}{Probate No. }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{................}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084\sa0\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{In the Estate of}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~}}}{NOTICE OF PROBATE OF WILL,}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084\sa0\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{....................}}}{, Deceased }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~}}}{OF APPOINTMENT OF }\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084\sa0\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~}}}{EXECUTOR, AND}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084\sa0\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~\~}}}{NOTICE TO CREDITORS}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084\sa0\par}{}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084\sa0\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{To All Persons Interested in the Estate of }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{........................}}}{, Deceased, who died on or about }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{................}}}{ (date):}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084\sa0\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{You are hereby notified that on the }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{........}}}{ day of }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{............}}}{ (month), }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{............}}}{ (year), the last will and testament of }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{........................}}}{, deceased, bearing the date of the }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{........}}}{ day of }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{............}}}{ (month), }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{............}}}{ (year), was admitted to probate in the above-named court and that }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{........................}}}{ was appointed executor of the estate. Any action to set aside the will must be brought in the district court of said county within the later to occur of four months from the date of the second publication of this notice or one month from the date of mailing of this notice to all heirs of the decedent and devisees under the will whose identities are reasonably ascertainable, or thereafter be forever barred.}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084\sa0\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{Notice is further given that all persons indebted to the estate are requested to make immediate payment to the undersigned, and creditors having claims against the estate shall file them with the clerk of the above-named district court, as provided by law, duly authenticated, for allowance, and, unless so filed by the later to occur of four months from the date of second publication of this notice or one month from the date of mailing of this notice (unless otherwise allowed or paid), a claim is thereafter forever barred.}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084\sa0\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{Dated this }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{........}}}{ day of }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{............}}}{ (month), }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{............}}}{ (year)}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084\sa0\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{........................}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084\sa0\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084{Executor of estate}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084\sa0\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{................................}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084\sa0\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084{Address}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084\sa0\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{........................}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084\sa0\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084{Attorney for executor}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084\sa0\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{................................}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084\sa0\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri1084\li1084{Address}\par}{\pard\plai